<HTML><BODY style="word-wrap: break-word; -khtml-nbsp-mode: space; -khtml-line-break: after-white-space; ">This is what I have just discovered - mpicc didn't have -m32 in it.<DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV>Thanks for the other info (config list)!</DIV><DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV>-david</DIV><DIV><BR><DIV><DIV>On Apr 10, 2006, at 8:56 AM, Jeff Squyres ((jsquyres)) wrote:</DIV><BR class="Apple-interchange-newline"><BLOCKQUOTE type="cite"><P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">The extra "-m32" was necessary because the wrapper compiler did not</FONT></P> <P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">include the CFLAGS from the configure line (we don't do this by default</FONT></P> <P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">on the assumption that you may want to build Open MPI with different</FONT></P> <P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">flags than your MPI executables).<SPAN class="Apple-converted-space">  </SPAN>You can get the wrapper compilers to</FONT></P> <P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">automatically include additional flags by supplying</FONT></P> <P style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px"><FONT face="Helvetica" size="3" style="font: 12.0px Helvetica">--with-wrapper-[cflags|cxxflags|...].<SPAN class="Apple-converted-space"> </SPAN></FONT></P> </BLOCKQUOTE></DIV><BR></DIV></BODY></HTML>
